1
00:00:20,083 --> 00:00:21,200
And the promise I once made

2
00:00:21,350 --> 00:00:23,960
to liberate Ayutthaya from its vassal status

3
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:26,000
can no longer be fulfilled.

4
00:00:26,371 --> 00:00:29,040
I shall hold a grand royal wedding

5
00:00:29,237 --> 00:00:32,080
for Crown Prince Mingyi Swa

6
00:00:32,330 --> 00:00:36,280
and Princess Natshin Medaw of Inwa, within the coming month.

7
00:00:37,723 --> 00:00:38,760
In the past,

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,720
I have been far too lenient with you.

9
00:00:42,110 --> 00:00:45,120
I have been ordered to Martaban.

10
00:00:47,823 --> 00:00:48,824
Father!

11
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,200
I yield!

12
00:00:51,877 --> 00:00:53,360
If you can endure it no longer, then come with me.

13
00:00:53,497 --> 00:00:55,720
Within the walls of Phitsanulok, I am the sovereign.

14
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,720
I shall not allow anyone to harm you, Brother.

15
00:00:57,850 --> 00:00:59,960
Even the walls of Ayutthaya,

16
00:01:00,123 --> 00:01:02,760
can hope to stand against the King of Hongsawadi.

17
00:01:02,977 --> 00:01:06,080
For me, freedom

18
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,600
is within my reach.

19
00:01:10,243 --> 00:01:11,920
but for Mingyi Swa,

20
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:13,681
Freedom...

21
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,800
has slipped through his hands.

22
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,281
Forgive me.

23
00:02:18,143 --> 00:02:19,240
This song is too sorrowful.

24
00:02:21,657 --> 00:02:22,760
I do not wish to play it any longer.

25
00:02:27,743 --> 00:02:29,600
Any new song will likely be just as sorrowful as the last,

26
00:02:35,510 --> 00:02:37,920
for that sadness stems from the heart of the player themselves.

27
00:03:02,390 --> 00:03:03,560
In this world,

28
00:03:05,397 --> 00:03:07,240
How many people are torn apart?

29
00:03:08,997 --> 00:03:10,600
How many people find their hearts' desire?

30
00:03:12,143 --> 00:03:16,280
That we two can still see each other,

31
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:19,120
and still play the harp together,

32
00:03:21,863 --> 00:03:23,440
is already a blessing.

33
00:03:25,077 --> 00:03:26,240
Why should we dwell in sorrow?

34
00:03:45,970 --> 00:03:47,040
people speak in whispers

35
00:03:49,143 --> 00:03:51,680
that Princess Yaza Datu Kalaya is the fairest in Pagan.

36
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:59,640
They do not know that your true beauty

37
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,561
is not found in your countenance,

38
00:04:05,663 --> 00:04:06,800
but within your heart.

39
00:04:14,517 --> 00:04:15,518
I understand now.

40
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,800
Let us continue to play the harp.

41
00:04:58,083 --> 00:04:59,084
Ouch!

42
00:05:13,270 --> 00:05:17,800
Have you thought this through, to become the consort of Mingyi Swa?

43
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,041
Yes, Father.

44
00:05:22,537 --> 00:05:26,620
Today, I may be but the consort of the Crown Prince.

45
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,361
But in the days to come,

46
00:05:30,677 --> 00:05:33,600
Mingyi Swa shall be the Lord of Hongsawadi.

47
00:05:36,678 --> 00:05:38,280
But power resides in the hands of men.

48
00:05:39,550 --> 00:05:42,280
If ever there comes a day when Mingyi Swa no longer feels affection for you,

49
00:05:43,477 --> 00:05:45,640
that power may very well fall into the hands of another woman.

50
00:05:50,457 --> 00:05:51,458
That is True, My Lord.

51
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,360
Real Power may indeed reside in the hands of Men.

52
00:06:09,770 --> 00:06:13,240
And if Mingyi Swa does not grant it to me willingly,

53
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:16,120
then surely my Royal Father

54
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,360
must seize it for me.

55
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:50,880
You appear to be in high spirits.

56
00:07:52,537 --> 00:07:53,880
Where have you been?

57
00:07:54,437 --> 00:07:56,360
You surely know well within your heart

58
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,520
exactly where I have been.

59
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:03,000
If that be the case, then there is no need for evasion.

60
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:16,920
I strictly forbid you from playing the harp ever again.

61
00:08:24,950 --> 00:08:26,960
You have no right to command me.

62
00:08:29,817 --> 00:08:31,680
Can I truly not command you?

63
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:38,000
Even when you did not wish to wed me,

64
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:40,600
you were still forced to do so.

65
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,323
We two were wed

66
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:52,360
because Hongsawadi sought to forge an alliance with Inwa.

67
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:57,290
Though I do not love you, I honor you as my consort.

68
00:08:58,377 --> 00:09:00,720
But in matters that bring me happiness,

69
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:03,720
you must not interfere.

70
00:09:12,197 --> 00:09:13,198
No way, Your Highness.

71
00:09:13,623 --> 00:09:16,560
Why? What is it that you truly desire?

72
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:22,480
Besides being the woman with the supreme power in Hongsawadi,

73
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:27,080
what I truly desire

74
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,360
is to see you suffer.

75
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:34,560
Whatever you hold dear,

76
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,800
I shall obstruct.

77
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:39,700
I will never allow you to find happiness or joy.

78
00:09:44,297 --> 00:09:46,040
- Give it to me.
- No!

79
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,121
Sister.

80
00:10:26,103 --> 00:10:28,600
We have reason to visit Hongsawadi at this time.

81
00:10:29,037 --> 00:10:30,038
Yes, Your Majesty.

82
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:44,160
Thado Minsaw has sent a message to us.

83
00:10:44,690 --> 00:10:47,360
He claims you harmed the consort until she bled.

84
00:10:47,691 --> 00:10:48,692
What is the meaning of this?

85
00:10:52,430 --> 00:10:56,120
I did not harm her. She fell on her own.

86
00:10:57,070 --> 00:10:58,400
It was an unavoidable accident, Your Majesty.

87
00:11:00,157 --> 00:11:03,400
Thado Minsaw naturally believes his daughter, not you.

88
00:11:04,583 --> 00:11:07,640
The message states the princess is deeply aggrieved.

89
00:11:08,437 --> 00:11:12,040
Her father is coming to Hongsawadi to take her back to Inwa.

90
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,161
The blood-stained cloth

91
00:11:25,843 --> 00:11:28,000
and the grievances written in the message.

92
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,800
These are nothing more than a strategic ploy.

93
00:11:35,110 --> 00:11:36,560
Using this as a pretext,

94
00:11:37,090 --> 00:11:39,120
King Thado Minsaw now has an excuse

95
00:11:39,230 --> 00:11:41,360
to mobilize his troops and advance upon Hongsawadi.

96
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,560
It is the same old trick as before.

97
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:50,440
It is not that I am unaware of Thado Minsaw's intent to rebel.

98
00:11:51,270 --> 00:11:55,080
I thought marrying Natshin Medaw would ensure some mutual respect.

99
00:11:56,920 --> 00:12:00,160
This time, it is because you failed to manage your own household.

100
00:12:00,963 --> 00:12:02,760
Now it has brought trouble upon the kingdom.

101
00:12:03,310 --> 00:12:04,560
What do you intend to do about this?

102
00:12:11,390 --> 00:12:14,200
- I beg your forgiveness, Your Majesty...
- What is it? Speak quickly.

103
00:12:15,023 --> 00:12:18,480
Our scouts have reported that the forces of Inwa are on the move, Your Majesty.

104
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:23,480
Perhaps Inwa has been at peace for too long.

105
00:12:24,623 --> 00:12:26,760
Thado Minsaw seems remarkably thirsty for war.

106
00:12:28,490 --> 00:12:29,491
Good.

107
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:33,040
Since he wants war, let us fight to our heart's content.

108
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:38,040
King Nanda Bayin has issued a royal command.

109
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:41,840
Gather the troops to prepare the grand army.

110
00:12:42,123 --> 00:12:45,480
His Majesty will lead the campaign against King Thado Minsaw of Inwa

111
00:12:46,124 --> 00:12:47,480
himself.

112
00:12:58,497 --> 00:13:00,040
I pay my respects, Father.

113
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:03,440
I sent you to oversee the road builders in the forest.

114
00:13:03,903 --> 00:13:05,680
Why have you returned without being called?

115
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,241
I have an urgent matter to report.

116
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,840
What matter is so urgent that it must be discussed now?

117
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:29,360
I fear the message will reach Mingyi Swa.

118
00:13:31,037 --> 00:13:32,120
Regarding Prince Nares?

119
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,120
I stayed outside

120
00:13:37,297 --> 00:13:39,700
and conducted my own reconnaissance.

121
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:44,560
I have discovered that Prince Nares has formed a private guard

122
00:13:45,337 --> 00:13:47,320
comprised only of the most skilled warriors.

123
00:13:49,117 --> 00:13:50,118
I fear

124
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,240
he is planning something significant.

125
00:13:54,537 --> 00:13:56,000
I have hurried here to inform you

126
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:59,800
so that you might extinguish the flame before it spreads.

127
00:14:06,478 --> 00:14:11,120
And he has commanded me to lead the troops from Phitsanulok

128
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:12,920
to assist in the battle.

129
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:19,120
You return and inform the King of Hongsawadi

130
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,600
That I, the Lord of Phitsanulok,

131
00:14:22,157 --> 00:14:26,640
shall obey the royal command and lead my army to the war in Inwa immediately.

132
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,601
Yes, Your Highness.

133
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:47,080
If you wish to extinguish the flame before it spreads,

134
00:14:48,057 --> 00:14:49,600
how do you suggest I proceed?

135
00:14:52,077 --> 00:14:53,078
Last time,

136
00:14:54,537 --> 00:14:57,560
You sent him to war and ordered his assassination

137
00:14:58,290 --> 00:14:59,920
once the battle was won.

138
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:03,640
I failed then, and so he survived.

139
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:08,840
For this campaign against Inwa,

140
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:13,360
If that captive joins the fight, I ask for a second chance.

141
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,120
Is that so?

142
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:24,200
I shall have you join me in the campaign against Inwa,

143
00:15:26,390 --> 00:15:29,080
And let Mingyi Swa remain here to guard the city in our stead.

144
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:32,880
Without Brother here to interfere,

145
00:15:34,483 --> 00:15:36,600
that captive will certainly not survive, Your Majesty.

146
00:15:44,570 --> 00:15:47,200
One the 6th waning moon, 3rd month,

147
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:48,531
The year of the goat,

148
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:52,040
I led an army of 300 elephants,

149
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:56,080
3,000 horses, and 60,000 infantry

150
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:58,000
out of Phitsanulok

151
00:15:58,290 --> 00:16:02,840
to join the forces of Hongsawadi in the war against Inwa.

152
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:08,360
We shall reach Inwa in no more than two months.

153
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,520
Prince Nares’s army has departed from Phitsanulok

154
00:16:11,750 --> 00:16:13,120
And will likely arrive after us.

155
00:16:15,317 --> 00:16:18,880
Once he arrives, how do you intend to strike?

156
00:16:19,376 --> 00:16:23,240
This time Nares is not alone as before.

157
00:16:24,470 --> 00:16:25,920
If anything happens to him,

158
00:16:27,097 --> 00:16:30,280
the soldiers following him will not remain idle.

159
00:16:31,337 --> 00:16:32,640
I have a plan.

160
00:16:34,797 --> 00:16:36,240
I shall mix poison

161
00:16:37,343 --> 00:16:39,196
into their water for them to drink,

162
00:16:40,717 --> 00:16:42,440
to kill every last one of them.

163
00:16:44,118 --> 00:16:47,640
That way, none shall remain to cause trouble.

164
00:16:49,883 --> 00:16:53,080
Let us target only Prince Nares and his officers.

165
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:59,480
As for the remaining troops, if they pledge allegiance, keep them for service.

166
00:17:01,323 --> 00:17:02,440
But if they refuse,

167
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:05,200
execute them all.

168
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:12,161
[The outskirts of Muang Krang]

169
00:17:24,830 --> 00:17:25,831
This is a fine place.

170
00:17:26,370 --> 00:17:29,120
There is water and fish, and food is plenty.

171
00:17:29,930 --> 00:17:32,600
Let us rest comfortably for 2-3 days before we continue our journey.

172
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:38,440
Yes, Your Highness. To speak the truth,

173
00:17:41,643 --> 00:17:43,920
every step I take forward feels like a step back.

174
00:17:45,350 --> 00:17:46,680
I have no desire to reach Inwa at all.

175
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:53,280
I know, but we have been summoned.

176
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,560
If we do not go, will we not be branded as rebels?

177
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:59,240
It pains me to waste our troops, elephants, and horses.

178
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:01,400
We spent such effort training our soldiers,

179
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:06,960
only to have them die for Hongsawadi.

180
00:18:07,917 --> 00:18:09,280
It is deeply frustrating to think about.

181
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:19,641
Right.

182
00:18:27,797 --> 00:18:28,798
Father,

183
00:18:29,613 --> 00:18:33,640
the armies of Prome, Toungoo, and Lan Xang

184
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:35,840
have all arrived and are assembled.

185
00:18:36,803 --> 00:18:41,480
Only the armies of Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya remain.

186
00:18:42,477 --> 00:18:43,970
A message has arrived from them.

187
00:18:45,910 --> 00:18:48,640
Prince Nares left Phitsanulok since the 3rd month.

188
00:18:49,323 --> 00:18:52,870
It is now the 6th month, yet they have only just reached Muang Krang.

189
00:18:56,770 --> 00:18:58,100
Why are they so slow?

190
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,520
They claim there are reasons,

191
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,700
but I do not believe them.

192
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:09,200
Duang, write to them that

193
00:19:09,670 --> 00:19:11,360
my march was delayed

194
00:19:15,323 --> 00:19:16,324
because of...

195
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:19,561
clashing elephants.

196
00:19:20,117 --> 00:19:22,840
An ancient ill omen that forbids the march.

197
00:19:24,377 --> 00:19:27,480
Is this acceptable? Mention that an ill omen occurred.

198
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:32,160
Ming Muang, the royal elephant, became frenzied.

199
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:36,120
No. Do not curse Muang. It is ill-omened.

200
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:41,160
But the texts state the omen must occur to the royal elephant

201
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:43,160
to be truly considered a bad sign, Your Highness.

202
00:19:54,217 --> 00:19:55,218
Phet.

203
00:19:56,520 --> 00:19:58,200
I shall borrow your toy for a moment.

204
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:07,680
From this moment forth, you two shall have new names,

205
00:20:08,990 --> 00:20:12,360
Phlai Kaew Chakkarat and Phlai Sawatdimongkhon.

206
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:14,041
You are now my royal elephants.

207
00:20:14,830 --> 00:20:17,480
Your Highness, but they are only beetles.

208
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:20,320
If clay dolls can be used to represent people,

209
00:20:20,517 --> 00:20:22,137
then if I wish to grant rank to these beetles

210
00:20:22,303 --> 00:20:24,440
and call them elephants, that is my business.

211
00:20:25,643 --> 00:20:27,720
Duang, write this.

212
00:20:29,003 --> 00:20:32,640
Because Phlai Kaew Chakkarat

213
00:20:33,517 --> 00:20:35,480
clashed with Phlai Sawatdimongkhon,

214
00:20:36,477 --> 00:20:38,800
the astrologers have predicted a grave omen.

215
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:42,480
We must await an auspicious time to perform a cleansing ritual

216
00:20:42,737 --> 00:20:44,000
before the march can continue.

217
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:48,040
How is that? Is it sufficient?

218
00:20:51,143 --> 00:20:52,320
It is as you command, Your Highness.

219
00:20:53,977 --> 00:20:56,920
This time, Prince Nares may escape the march,

220
00:20:58,023 --> 00:21:00,200
But he shall not escape death.

221
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,241
[Wat Pa, Muang Krang]

222
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,760
Now Phra Maha Thera Khanchong

223
00:21:06,120 --> 00:21:08,440
has moved to stay at Wat Pa, Muang Krang.

224
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,240
Prince Nares has halted his army there,

225
00:21:11,578 --> 00:21:13,360
likely intending to pay respects to his mentor.

226
00:21:13,379 --> 00:21:15,080
Greetings, Sir.

227
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:24,280
Since he refuses to come and die here peacefully,

228
00:21:25,497 --> 00:21:27,480
he must then die at Muang Krang.

229
00:21:29,950 --> 00:21:32,000
Then I shall volunteer

230
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:34,321
to take his head for you.

231
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:38,880
No need. You stay here to help with the war.

232
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,360
As for Prince Nares,

233
00:21:44,543 --> 00:21:46,320
I already have someone in mind.

234
00:22:04,077 --> 00:22:06,000
You have stayed here for many a day now,

235
00:22:07,490 --> 00:22:10,080
and have yet to declare when you shall move the army to Inwa.

236
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,700
This war in Inwa is truly an internal affair,

237
00:22:15,497 --> 00:22:18,640
An uncle and nephew fighting for power. I will not waste our strength.

238
00:22:21,163 --> 00:22:23,164
Not going is desertion.

239
00:22:24,250 --> 00:22:25,640
Do you not fear the royal penalty?

240
00:22:27,023 --> 00:22:28,800
If I fear, I must fear forever.

241
00:22:29,270 --> 00:22:31,040
When will it ever end, Venerable Sir?

242
00:22:37,303 --> 00:22:38,600
The ancients say

243
00:22:39,617 --> 00:22:43,360
the sea, tusks and fangs, women,

244
00:22:44,010 --> 00:22:48,241
kings, and weapons, these five must never be underestimated.

245
00:22:49,567 --> 00:22:51,800
If you no longer fear King Nanda Bayin,

246
00:22:52,377 --> 00:22:53,930
then break ties once and for all.

247
00:22:54,903 --> 00:22:56,737
Do not provoke him, for it will only bring ruin.

248
00:23:04,103 --> 00:23:05,960
To battle King Nanda Bayin,

249
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:09,920
I fear not, even with fewer forces.

250
00:23:11,437 --> 00:23:13,008
But the reason I cannot yet break ties,

251
00:23:13,397 --> 00:23:15,648
is my concern for my sister and Mingyi Swa.

252
00:23:17,163 --> 00:23:18,880
I am at a loss, Venerable Sir,

253
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,560
and know not what I must do.

254
00:23:35,497 --> 00:23:37,498
I will not eat! Take it away!

255
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:54,560
What ails you? Why do you refuse to eat?

256
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:57,560
Held captive like a prisoner of war,

257
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:59,000
who could possibly have an appetite?

258
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:03,080
You started this war yourself.

259
00:24:03,290 --> 00:24:05,040
My father merely ordered your confinement.

260
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:07,960
It is great mercy that you were not punished.

261
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:12,560
Will you punish me? Will you truly punish me?

262
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:18,200
For this war, blame yourself and no one else.

263
00:24:19,043 --> 00:24:20,600
Had you been kind to me,

264
00:24:21,350 --> 00:24:23,800
- no one would have to die today.
- Do not make excuses.

265
00:24:25,310 --> 00:24:26,640
Your father seeks a reason for war,

266
00:24:26,983 --> 00:24:29,640
- aiming to seize Hongsawadi from my father.
- And is that wrong?

267
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:33,920
Hongsawadi, Prome,

268
00:24:33,977 --> 00:24:36,080
Martaban, Lan Xang, and Ayutthaya,

269
00:24:36,360 --> 00:24:37,880
we seized them all by force.

270
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:41,960
To the victor go the spoils.

271
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:45,680
Is it right for King Nanda Bayin

272
00:24:46,181 --> 00:24:47,182
to keep all power for himself?

273
00:24:56,083 --> 00:24:59,000
Mingyi Swa, come back! Mingyi Swa!

274
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:09,880
Now that Grandfather has passed, the provinces are indeed rebelling as predicted.

275
00:25:10,837 --> 00:25:11,838
Your Highness,

276
00:25:13,103 --> 00:25:16,680
a message has arrived from King Nanda Bayin. It is marked as urgent.

277
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:42,961
Your Highness.

278
00:25:46,503 --> 00:25:48,400
Prince Nares has defied the royal decree

279
00:25:49,722 --> 00:25:51,600
and refused to march his army to aid the war in Inwa.

280
00:25:53,430 --> 00:25:54,920
Father has commanded

281
00:25:56,190 --> 00:25:58,120
that I decide on his execution,

282
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:00,800
to ensure no one else dares to follow his example.

283
00:26:06,117 --> 00:26:07,118
Your Highness.

284
00:26:07,883 --> 00:26:08,884
Your Highness.

285
00:26:11,310 --> 00:26:12,311
Wait, Your Highness.

286
00:26:12,637 --> 00:26:14,000
You must go and prepare yourself.

287
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:16,280
I depart for Muang Krang at once.

288
00:26:16,477 --> 00:26:17,478
It is not possible, Your Highness.

289
00:26:18,037 --> 00:26:20,200
While the King of Hongsawadi is away,

290
00:26:20,810 --> 00:26:22,440
you are the Crown Prince.

291
00:26:22,957 --> 00:26:24,600
You must remain as his representative

292
00:26:24,850 --> 00:26:27,000
and cannot depart from Hongsawadi, Your Highness.

293
00:26:27,010 --> 00:26:29,320
But my father has ordered Prince Nares's execution.

294
00:26:30,217 --> 00:26:31,760
How can I just sit idly by?

295
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,680
That sounds like fun.

296
00:26:38,641 --> 00:26:40,480
Let me accompany you, Brother.

297
00:26:42,397 --> 00:26:44,280
I want to see you execute Prince Nares.

298
00:26:46,937 --> 00:26:50,800
I am going to investigate the truth, not to execute anyone.

299
00:26:51,323 --> 00:26:54,560
How can that be? Father has ordered an execution.

300
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,040
You must carry it out.

301
00:26:58,210 --> 00:27:01,480
Or do you intend to defy a royal decree, Your Highness?

302
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:07,921
Mind your tongue.

303
00:27:31,210 --> 00:27:34,480
What the younger prince says is reasonable, Your Highness.

304
00:27:35,877 --> 00:27:39,320
A royal decree for execution has been issued. Therefore, the execution must proceed.

305
00:27:45,003 --> 00:27:46,004
I know.

306
00:27:48,450 --> 00:27:51,960
If I refrain, it is not only a violation of the law

307
00:27:52,683 --> 00:27:53,720
and military discipline,

308
00:27:57,070 --> 00:27:58,720
But it is also an insult to the royal authority

309
00:27:59,997 --> 00:28:02,160
and a dishonor to the King of Hongsawadi.

310
00:28:08,830 --> 00:28:10,920
But Prince Nares and I are like brothers.

311
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:13,880
How can I do such a thing?

312
00:28:19,283 --> 00:28:20,480
How about this, Your Highness?

313
00:28:22,223 --> 00:28:24,880
I shall volunteer for the task.

314
00:28:31,457 --> 00:28:32,560
Volunteer for what?

315
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:35,760
Since you cannot defy the royal decree,

316
00:28:36,943 --> 00:28:38,840
yet you cannot bring yourself to execute Prince Nares,

317
00:28:40,083 --> 00:28:43,240
I shall volunteer to handle this matter for you, Your highness.

318
00:28:53,483 --> 00:28:55,484
[Wat Pa, Muang Krang]

319
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:58,920
It is a royal decree.

320
00:29:00,120 --> 00:29:02,156
I myself cannot ignore it.

321
00:29:03,283 --> 00:29:05,480
Therefore, I would like to invite you, my brother, to come

322
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:09,960
to consult and find a way to lighten the burden of this situation.

323
00:29:13,757 --> 00:29:15,500
Is that what you wish? For me to come and see you, Brother?

324
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:17,281
Yes, Your Highness.

325
00:29:32,357 --> 00:29:33,840
Why must you go alone, Your Highness?

326
00:29:34,303 --> 00:29:37,480
Brother has ordered that this be kept secret. No one else must know.

327
00:29:38,750 --> 00:29:41,520
But what if danger befalls you along the way?

328
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:45,480
Mangjaparo is going along, and his skills are not to be underestimated.

329
00:29:46,280 --> 00:29:48,720
But regardless, he is not one of us, Your Highness.

330
00:29:55,297 --> 00:29:58,120
Since Brother sent him, he should be trustworthy.

331
00:29:59,563 --> 00:30:02,120
Enough, you need not be afraid.

332
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:03,840
I shall go quietly.

333
00:30:07,157 --> 00:30:11,158
Besides us, no one shall know.

334
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:43,441
Surround them!

335
00:30:58,478 --> 00:30:59,479
Who are you?

336
00:31:08,237 --> 00:31:09,560
Archers, ready!

337
00:31:26,023 --> 00:31:27,024
Prepare to fire!

338
00:31:36,217 --> 00:31:39,000
Tell me, for what reason do you intend to kill me?

339
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,321
Who sent you?

340
00:32:06,010 --> 00:32:07,011
Stop!

341
00:32:13,577 --> 00:32:14,578
Your Holiness.

342
00:32:17,830 --> 00:32:21,320
Stop it, Phraya Kian and Phraya Ram.

343
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:27,301
[Phraya Kian]

344
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,850
[Phraya Ram]

345
00:32:43,177 --> 00:32:46,280
Phraya Kian and Phraya Ram serve here.

346
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:50,440
They are my disciples, and we share the same Mon lineage.

347
00:32:55,010 --> 00:32:56,230
I have heard that

348
00:32:56,630 --> 00:32:59,610
Prince Nares is also a chief disciple of Phra Maha Thera.

349
00:32:59,870 --> 00:33:02,880
When I received the order to harm you,

350
00:33:03,537 --> 00:33:06,680
I hurried to bring the matter to consult with His Holiness.

351
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:09,721
Has someone ordered my death, then?

352
00:33:11,957 --> 00:33:12,958
Yes, Your Highness.

353
00:33:14,017 --> 00:33:17,200
They both did not wish to do it, but they did not dare disobey the orders.

354
00:33:17,663 --> 00:33:19,480
I therefore told them to pretend that

355
00:33:19,670 --> 00:33:22,210
they had attempted to assassinate you, but failed.

356
00:33:22,357 --> 00:33:25,200
Who ordered it? Was it that Mangjaparo?

357
00:33:32,417 --> 00:33:36,240
Mangjaparo was only following the orders of his master.

358
00:33:38,290 --> 00:33:40,120
And as for who that master is,

359
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:43,920
Your Highness knows full well.

360
00:33:59,323 --> 00:34:00,324
Brother.

361
00:34:25,163 --> 00:34:26,164
Nares.

362
00:34:27,883 --> 00:34:28,884
The two of us,

363
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:34,160
will we be on the same side forever?

364
00:34:35,990 --> 00:34:37,560
If you stand by my side,

365
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:40,400
I shall stand by yours.

366
00:34:43,297 --> 00:34:45,040
Take it as a word of honor.

367
00:34:54,917 --> 00:34:56,440
Take it as a word of honor.

368
00:35:05,463 --> 00:35:06,464
Brother.

369
00:35:34,560 --> 00:35:37,270
I have heard that you ordered a flogging

370
00:35:37,543 --> 00:35:41,800
and the imprisonment of the royal tutor Mangjaparo. For what reason?

371
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:43,840
I sent a message to Prince Nares,

372
00:35:44,630 --> 00:35:46,280
inviting him to come and negotiate.

373
00:35:47,420 --> 00:35:51,440
Along the way, Mangjaparo instead ordered men to lie in wait and attack,

374
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:53,881
intending to take Prince Nares's life.

375
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:56,760
Is it possible?

376
00:35:57,977 --> 00:36:00,320
The royal tutor is so deeply loyal.

377
00:36:00,983 --> 00:36:02,080
Why would he dare?

378
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:05,960
His loyalty is to my royal father,

379
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,040
not to me.

380
00:36:10,117 --> 00:36:13,120
Fortunately, Prince Nares was unharmed.

381
00:36:14,697 --> 00:36:15,698
At this moment,

382
00:36:16,710 --> 00:36:18,640
he likely believes Hongsawadi attempted to assassinate him

383
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:22,080
and must be deeply resentful toward me.

384
00:36:28,921 --> 00:36:30,100
But this time,

385
00:36:31,790 --> 00:36:34,200
Even if Prince Nares was fortunate enough to escape,

386
00:36:39,603 --> 00:36:41,520
he will still not evade the death penalty.

387
00:36:45,210 --> 00:36:47,000
I have sent a fast courier with a message to clarify the matter,

388
00:36:47,970 --> 00:36:49,720
hoping to find a way to ease the situation.

389
00:36:52,737 --> 00:36:57,080
But I do not know if Nares will let his anger subside and listen to me at all.

390
00:37:17,903 --> 00:37:20,520
Even if the Crown Prince Mingyi Swa

391
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:23,761
did not intend to harm or take my life,

392
00:37:25,483 --> 00:37:26,600
at this moment,

393
00:37:27,537 --> 00:37:29,040
I am deemed guilty

394
00:37:30,077 --> 00:37:32,880
of treachery and rebellion against King Nanda Bayin,

395
00:37:34,590 --> 00:37:36,881
And the death penalty is unavoidable.

396
00:37:55,899 --> 00:37:57,700
The time has come, Your Holiness.

397
00:38:03,560 --> 00:38:06,521
That I shall be free.

398
00:38:41,710 --> 00:38:43,360
Gods and deities

399
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:46,240
who dwell in every direction,

400
00:38:47,397 --> 00:38:49,320
Come and bear divine witness.

401
00:38:50,163 --> 00:38:54,120
As the King of Hongsawadi has not acted in good faith

402
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:57,081
and has brought harm upon us,

403
00:38:58,123 --> 00:38:59,480
I hereby declare

404
00:39:00,477 --> 00:39:03,478
The cities of Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya

405
00:39:04,080 --> 00:39:07,181
and the city of Hongsawadi to be severed,

406
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:12,045
From this day forth until the end of time.

407
00:40:03,997 --> 00:40:05,998
[Sanphet Prasat Throne Hall, Ayutthaya]

408
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:14,600
- Khao.
- Hurry, Mother! Come quickly and listen to the great news.

409
00:40:14,670 --> 00:40:15,920
Ouch, stop for a moment!

410
00:40:16,103 --> 00:40:17,104
What is it, Mother?

411
00:40:17,520 --> 00:40:18,680
What news is this?

412
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:20,500
Is it good or bad?

413
00:40:21,210 --> 00:40:22,537
It is news from Brother Nares.

414
00:40:23,237 --> 00:40:26,560
Phra Sri Thamorat has just come to have an audience and inform Father.

415
00:40:27,120 --> 00:40:28,640
Come, in that case, let us hurry.

416
00:40:28,810 --> 00:40:30,000
- Go.
- Yes, Mother.

417
00:40:32,763 --> 00:40:34,840
Queen Wisut Kasattri has arrived just in time.

418
00:40:41,510 --> 00:40:43,400
What news has our son sent, Your Majesty?

419
00:40:44,797 --> 00:40:46,480
On the 2nd day of the waning moon in the 6th month,

420
00:40:48,223 --> 00:40:50,080
Prince Nares poured the water of consecration,

421
00:40:51,403 --> 00:40:53,320
calling upon the gods of heaven and earth to witness

422
00:40:55,103 --> 00:40:57,120
that Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya

423
00:40:58,120 --> 00:41:00,480
shall no longer be subject to Hongsawadi.

424
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:02,680
We are free at last.

425
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:06,160
We are free.

426
00:41:11,520 --> 00:41:12,521
We are free.

427
00:41:16,717 --> 00:41:20,480
If King Nanda Bayin learns of this, he will certainly not allow it.

428
00:41:24,962 --> 00:41:28,120
What preparations has Prince Nares made, Phra Sri Thamorat?

429
00:41:30,645 --> 00:41:32,440
He has commanded me to inform you,

430
00:41:32,970 --> 00:41:34,920
asking Ayutthaya to levy troops and prepare provisions,

431
00:41:35,640 --> 00:41:37,360
and to secure the forts, moats, and city gates firmly.

432
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:39,882
He anticipates that a great war will certainly occur, Your Majesty.

433
00:41:42,830 --> 00:41:44,100
We also see it as such.

434
00:41:46,360 --> 00:41:47,361
Chao Khao,

435
00:41:49,183 --> 00:41:51,880
Help one another prepare everything and have it all ready.

436
00:41:52,450 --> 00:41:53,670
I receive your command with the greatest respect, Your Majesty.

437
00:41:54,530 --> 00:41:55,531
Wait.

438
00:41:57,431 --> 00:41:59,000
What about Princess Suphankalaya?

439
00:42:00,083 --> 00:42:03,640
She and her child are still being held hostage there.

440
00:42:04,243 --> 00:42:08,440
If war breaks out, what will become of our daughter and grandchild?

441
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:14,920
May it please Your Majesty, at this moment King Nanda Bayin and the royal army

442
00:42:15,177 --> 00:42:16,600
Are still waging war at Inwa.

443
00:42:17,030 --> 00:42:20,440
Prince Nares has seized this opportunity to lead his forces toward Hongsawadi, Your Majesty.

444
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:23,201
What?

445
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:27,001
No one is more impatient than my brother.

446
00:42:29,883 --> 00:42:31,300
There is no need to worry now, Mother.

447
00:42:31,884 --> 00:42:33,920
Someone has already hurried to bring our sister home.

448
00:42:58,597 --> 00:42:59,598
Phet.

449
00:43:00,043 --> 00:43:01,044
Wait here.

450
00:43:01,442 --> 00:43:02,443
Yes, Your Highness.

451
00:43:35,022 --> 00:43:36,023
Brother.

452
00:43:51,643 --> 00:43:52,644
I am glad

453
00:43:54,703 --> 00:43:56,204
That you still trust me.

454
00:44:00,160 --> 00:44:01,400
It is good that we have met,

455
00:44:03,183 --> 00:44:04,484
So that we may find a way to help one another.

456
00:44:05,443 --> 00:44:07,680
- To save you from the death penalty.
- That is not necessary, Brother.

457
00:44:10,383 --> 00:44:12,320
I no longer need to accept that punishment.

458
00:44:13,830 --> 00:44:14,831
Now,

459
00:44:15,263 --> 00:44:19,440
I am no longer a vassal ruler under the mandate of Hongsawadi.

460
00:44:22,417 --> 00:44:23,418
What is that you say?

461
00:44:28,163 --> 00:44:29,840
On the 2nd day of the waning moon in the 6th month,

462
00:44:31,683 --> 00:44:34,920
I poured the water of consecration to let the gods of heaven and earth witness

463
00:44:36,970 --> 00:44:38,880
that Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya

464
00:44:39,850 --> 00:44:41,920
shall no longer be subject to Hongsawadi.

465
00:44:50,677 --> 00:44:52,160
I am free now.

466
00:44:58,150 --> 00:44:59,280
But we once promised

467
00:45:00,997 --> 00:45:02,360
that we would stand by each other's side.

468
00:45:05,603 --> 00:45:07,604
If we are to stand by each other's side,

469
00:45:09,280 --> 00:45:12,600
we must stand shoulder to shoulder as equals like friends,

470
00:45:14,550 --> 00:45:16,050
Not with one as master

471
00:45:17,670 --> 00:45:19,300
and the other as servant.

472
00:45:37,053 --> 00:45:38,054
Then,

473
00:45:40,080 --> 00:45:41,440
as of now, the two of us

474
00:45:45,323 --> 00:45:47,080
stand on opposite sides, do we not?

475
00:46:14,310 --> 00:46:15,311
I have just received word

476
00:46:16,770 --> 00:46:19,240
That the Hongsawadi army has just triumphed over Inwa.

477
00:46:22,560 --> 00:46:24,161
My father is in high spirits.

478
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:26,820
If he learns of your rebellion,

479
00:46:28,637 --> 00:46:29,840
you will certainly face a heavy onslaught.

480
00:46:31,363 --> 00:46:34,400
If it cannot be avoided, then so be it.

481
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:38,050
I would like to make a request of you, Brother.

482
00:46:39,343 --> 00:46:41,680
I wish to take my sister back to Ayutthaya.

483
00:46:59,203 --> 00:47:01,280
And what if I cannot grant that?

484
00:47:04,160 --> 00:47:08,800
I have 6,000 troops currently outside the walls of Hongsawadi.

485
00:47:09,503 --> 00:47:10,680
If necessary,

486
00:47:11,697 --> 00:47:14,440
I will break through to bring my sister back at any cost.

487
00:47:20,823 --> 00:47:21,824
Would you

488
00:47:24,417 --> 00:47:25,920
wage war against me?

489
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:28,601
Brother.

490
00:47:40,600 --> 00:47:42,680
I shall take my sister home.

491
00:47:43,720 --> 00:47:45,840
If you help me,

492
00:47:47,937 --> 00:47:50,080
I shall have no need to fight anyone.

493
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:11,141
Prince Nares will be waiting at the Phra Maha Thera's old temple.

494
00:48:12,010 --> 00:48:15,670
This temple is deserted. I will send someone to invite Your Highness

495
00:48:16,343 --> 00:48:17,880
to escape secretly through the rear of the palace.

496
00:48:18,797 --> 00:48:21,150
Take me away secretly through the rear of the palace?

497
00:48:24,800 --> 00:48:26,160
But what of Min A Htwe

498
00:48:28,001 --> 00:48:30,520
And the people in my residence?

499
00:48:33,342 --> 00:48:34,360
Min A Htwe

500
00:48:35,543 --> 00:48:38,921
is a royal daughter who carries the bloodline of the Grandfather;

501
00:48:40,970 --> 00:48:42,880
She cannot be allowed to go to Ayutthaya.

502
00:48:46,343 --> 00:48:50,360
Only Your Highness and the attendants who followed you may return.

503
00:48:52,783 --> 00:48:54,080
This matter is a secret.

504
00:48:55,437 --> 00:48:57,400
It cannot be done with such fanfare that others find out.

505
00:49:00,070 --> 00:49:02,040
When shall we depart?

506
00:49:03,063 --> 00:49:04,064
In five days,

507
00:49:05,570 --> 00:49:06,871
Prince Nares will be waiting to receive you.

508
00:49:08,457 --> 00:49:09,960
Please have yourself prepared and ready.

509
00:49:26,040 --> 00:49:27,520
I, Mingyi Naung,

510
00:49:28,870 --> 00:49:32,720
humbly pay homage before the feet of the King of Hongsawadi, Nanda Bayin,

511
00:49:33,440 --> 00:49:34,441
my royal father.

512
00:50:11,983 --> 00:50:13,400
It is time, Your Highness.

513
00:50:29,803 --> 00:50:32,760
Please depart, Your Highness. Do not worry for me.

514
00:50:45,163 --> 00:50:46,400
Alas, my dear,

515
00:50:49,080 --> 00:50:53,521
If you must remain alone, how shall you live?

516
00:50:54,110 --> 00:50:55,722
I can survive, Your Highness.

517
00:50:56,797 --> 00:50:59,240
Prince Mingyi Swa said I am already grown.

518
00:51:00,233 --> 00:51:03,080
In a few years, I must be wed and move to another city,

519
00:51:04,323 --> 00:51:06,000
and would not be living with Mother anyway.

520
00:51:15,120 --> 00:51:16,320
It is true, my child.

521
00:51:18,910 --> 00:51:21,040
If we do not stay together now,

522
00:51:22,857 --> 00:51:25,080
we likely shall not be together ever again.

523
00:52:27,563 --> 00:52:28,920
Why have you come alone?

524
00:52:30,023 --> 00:52:32,800
And what of your personal belongings?

525
00:52:36,340 --> 00:52:37,400
I have come to bid farewell.

526
00:52:40,523 --> 00:52:41,524
What?

527
00:52:46,943 --> 00:52:48,480
Thank you very much, Dam,

528
00:52:49,817 --> 00:52:50,920
for not forgetting me,

529
00:52:53,720 --> 00:52:56,320
and for venturing to Hongsawadi to receive me.

530
00:52:58,720 --> 00:52:59,721
What is this?

531
00:53:02,063 --> 00:53:03,664
Do you not intend to return with me?

532
00:53:07,783 --> 00:53:10,880
I long to return to Ayutthaya with every breath,

533
00:53:13,623 --> 00:53:15,240
But I cannot leave my child

534
00:53:15,883 --> 00:53:17,920
And my attendants behind.

535
00:53:25,963 --> 00:53:27,880
Allowing the royal sister to return with you

536
00:53:29,383 --> 00:53:30,520
is already improper.

537
00:53:33,983 --> 00:53:37,520
If the Royal Daughter, born of King Bayinnaung, were also taken back,

538
00:53:39,440 --> 00:53:41,400
Hongsawadi would surely never permit it.

539
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:50,880
Ayutthaya is free now,

540
00:53:52,857 --> 00:53:54,640
But my sister still cannot be free.

541
00:53:56,170 --> 00:53:57,280
I am deeply saddened.

542
00:53:58,830 --> 00:53:59,831
Dam.

543
00:54:02,630 --> 00:54:04,631
This time, I have chosen for myself.

544
00:54:21,363 --> 00:54:23,440
I ask to send my heart

545
00:54:25,560 --> 00:54:26,800
along with You.

546
00:54:30,703 --> 00:54:33,600
In the future, if fate allows,

547
00:54:36,957 --> 00:54:40,000
I shall surely return to prostrate before the feet of Father and Mother.

548
00:55:33,240 --> 00:55:35,560
Step inside here for a day and reflect well

549
00:55:35,741 --> 00:55:37,572
on how you have wronged Hongsawadi.

550
00:55:38,037 --> 00:55:40,880
But I desire only to preserve the lives of the soldiers.

551
00:55:41,038 --> 00:55:44,720
In the endless cycle of killing, those who perish are the common people,

552
00:55:44,810 --> 00:55:46,200
not the rulers!

553
00:55:46,310 --> 00:55:49,120
Since you know this, do not let them die in vain!

554
00:55:49,480 --> 00:55:52,600
If we wish to be free, we cannot lose,

555
00:55:53,057 --> 00:55:54,360
not even once.

556
00:55:57,600 --> 00:55:58,601
What are you doing?
